    95	- Devnet: program `6pW64gN1s2uqjHkn1unFeEjAwJkPGHoppGvS715wyP2J`, API base `https://txline-dev.txodds.com/api/`, guest auth `https://txline-dev.txodds.com/auth/guest/start`. Mainnet: program `9ExbZjAapQww1vfcisDmrngPinHTEfpjYRWMunJgcKaA`, API base `https://txline.txodds.com/api/`. Never mix hosts across networks.
    96	- Two credentials per data request: `Authorization: Bearer <guest JWT>` (renewable) + `X-Api-Token: <activated token>`. 401 → renew JWT, same api token. 403 on activation → check message/wallet/network.
    97	- Runnable devnet examples (free-tier activation, odds/scores streams): https://txline.txodds.com/documentation/examples/devnet-examples
    98	- Docs index for machines: https://txline.txodds.com/llms.txt · API reference: https://txline.txodds.com/api-reference/authentication/start-a-new-guest-session
    99	- Support: Discord https://discord.gg/txodds · Telegram https://t.me/TxLINEChat (also the listing's official contact)
   100	
   101	## 5. The unwritten layer (verified against July 2026 recorded winners — assume it applies)
   102	
   103	The written rubric above decides who reaches the final. These decide who WINS:
   104	
   105	- [ ] **Real niche with a face** — a named person/business the judge can picture (use YOUR real company)
   106	- [ ] **Agentic framing** — an agent doing work autonomously within explicit policy bounds ("most of what wins is agentic AI" — organizer, on record) — *here it's the WRITTEN rubric too (criterion 2)*
   107	- [ ] **Sourced problem statistics** — 2–3 numbers judges can't argue with, spoken in the first 30 seconds
   108	- [ ] **One live wow moment** — a 10-second visible proof (live connect, real write landing, balance hitting zero)
   109	- [ ] **Human-in-the-loop as a trust feature** — approval gates presented as a strength, never an apology — *frame carefully: rubric demands "without manual input ONCE DEPLOYED"; gates belong at policy level, not per-decision*
   110	- [ ] **Sponsor-tool visibility** — TxLINE endpoints named on screen; the Solana anchoring shown, not just claimed
   111	- [ ] **3-minute comprehension** — a judge who missed the first 90 seconds can still explain the product
   112	- [ ] **Honest Q&A** — admitted gap + roadmap beat bluffing on record; prepare answers in `PITCH.md` (live interview round confirmed for this event)
   113	- [ ] **Feedback field is scored attention** — sponsor explicitly wants API friction reports; log every rough edge as we integrate and hand it in
   114	
   115	## 6. Anti-checklist (verified UNDER-rewarded on record — cap effort here)
   116	
   117	- Architecture depth / test count beyond green-and-stable (least-enforced axis in the recordings)
   118	- UI polish beyond the demo camera path
   119	- Feature breadth (the team challenged hardest overlapped an existing platform feature; "one killer feature beats five half-built ones")
   120	- Live activity during review — impossible anyway (matches end before judging); the ≤5-min video carries everything

